  <div id="intro" class="floating-section">
    <h2>Saturday March 6th 2021</h2>
    <h3>Course Description</h3>
    <p>
      The course is 20K in length starting at Maunawili Elementary School and finishing at Hanauma Bay State Park, racing on Kalaniana’ole Highway <strong>except through Waimanalo where the course will use back roads to avoid high traffic intersections</strong>. For full course details see the <a href="https://www.strava.com/segments/23101100">Castle to Hanauma Alternate Route Strava Segment</a>. To compete simply ride the course on Saturday March 6th between 6:00 A.M. and 3:00 P.M., record your ride with a GPS tracker, and either register with us using Strava, or upload you ride data (details to be provided). While there will not be any marshals on course to enforce TT rules, in the spirit of the event we encourage all riders to compete <strong>solo</strong> and avoid drafting. <strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> this ride is completely unsupported and you must follow the rules of the road and observe all traffic signage. Please watch out for pedestrians, cars, stray dogs, etc. Stay safe and healthy out there.</strong>
    </p>
